overview: The user initiated a request to fix a problematic pull request with
  multiple issues, including critical security flaws and failing Vercel
  deployments. The agent systematically tackled these, starting with lint errors
  and moving to more complex security vulnerabilities like forgeable admin
  cookies, which were resolved by implementing HMAC-based session tokens using
  the Web Crypto API for Edge Runtime compatibility. Data validation for API
  endpoints and CSV exports was enhanced, and several UI/UX bugs related to PDF
  generation and form fields were fixed. A significant challenge arose from
  Vercel deployment failures, first due to a missing database URL in the Prisma
  schema, and then a critical Next.js security vulnerability. Updating Next.js
  to version 16.1.1 introduced further breaking changes with Prisma 7 and the
  removal of the  command, necessitating additional configuration
  adjustments for Prisma and ESLint. The agent successfully navigated these
  cascading issues, ensuring the codebase was secure, functional, and compatible
  with the updated dependencies.
